MAH-seh-DOH-nee-a

===Etymology===
From ancient Greek [[μακεδονικός]] (''makedonikos'') "related to [[Macedonia]]".

===Proper noun===
'''Macedonian''' ([[Macedonians]])

#An inhabitant, resident, or a person of descent from the ancient Macedonian kingdom, the [[Greek Macedonia]], the [[Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia]] or Bulgarian Macedonia.
#An ancient Greek [[dialect]] that was spoken in the ancient Macedonian kingdom.
#A [[Slavic]] language (most likely a Bulgarian [[dialect]]) spoken in the Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia, south western [[Bulgaria]], northern parts of [[Greek Macedonia]], south eastern [[Serbia and Montenegro]], and parts of far eastern [[Albania]].

